<h2>Flicker</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Release Date:</strong> March 2016</li>
  <li><strong>Credits:</strong> Writer and Key Grip</li>
  <li><strong>Runtime:</strong> 5 minutes 39 seconds</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Synopsis:</strong> While this film is designed to be open for
    interpretation, it is generally helpful to understand it is a metaphorical
    adventure though the memories of the protagonist – an experimental narrative
    created with experimental filmmaking techniques.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Production Notes:</strong> This film was made for the Spring 2016
    Film48 competition at Binghamton University where teams are given prompts
    and then only 48-hours to write, shoot, edit, and finalize a short film.
    This film won the “Best Picture” and “Fan Favorite” awards for the Film48
    competition.
