<h2>Garden of Play</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Release Date:</strong> 2009</li>
  <li><strong>Credits:</strong> Cinematographer and Editor</li>
  <li><strong>Runtime:</strong> 1 minute 51 seconds</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Synopsis:</strong> Experimental film made in 2009 that explores a
    variety of cinematographic techniques including deep-focus and shallow-focus
    photography, time-lapse, high-speed photography (slow motion), and rhythmic
    editing to music.
    The title refers to both the content of the images and the filmmaker’s
    playful experimentations.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Production Notes:</strong> This film was shot in Colorado Springs
    with a Panasonic AG-DVX100 (DVCPRO HD), Letus35 lens adapter, and a variety
    of lenses. Edited and color graded with Final Cut Pro. The score came from a
    music library.
  </li>
</ul>

